inn1.comm: angled in to Finch from a good length, decent bounce, he tucks it to square leg
good line outside off stump, carries sharply through to the keeper as it is left alone
wider now, and comes in a bit, but easily left
pitches it up further, gets it to straighten, he pushes it to mid off
leans across and turns this length ball with the incoming angle to midwicket
hurries onto him and rises as he comes forward to defend, hits the pad high and flies to the slips
excellent start from Chatara, gets it to straighten and kick after angling it in, hits Haddin as he misses
moves across on the back foot this time and calmly defends a back of a length ball
pitched much further up, Haddin leans into the line to defend
combination of the inward angle and fuller length means he can clip this nicely off the legs through midwicket
Finch decides to leave this short of a length ball really late, almost takes the edge as it moves in
shout for lbw now, caught on the crease as this comes in with the angle, looked high, he was hopping too
leans well forward to push a good length ball outside off to covers
another tester, comes in sharply after pitching, but rises too much, catches him on the thigh pad
he is hesitant to move forward, manages to play this length ball to off from the crease
good length ball turned straight to midwicket with the angle
short of a good length, he lets it climb and guides it to point
hops, moves across, gets behind the line and defends a short of a length ball down the track
good length on off stump, turned to the right of mid on for a single
stays on the crease and pushes a shortish ball to cover, no chance of a single
nice, hint of straightening as he pitches it up just outside off, Haddin leans into it to block
similar delivery around off, a firm push this time from Haddin to mid off
leans across and plays it out close to the pitch on the leg side
sees a shorter length this time and swivels for the pull, not much pace off the wicket and he mistimes it to midwicket
tentatively pushes a short of a length ball down the track, hit close to the splice there, bowler fields
neatly forward this time to push a length ball to cover
with runs not coming the conventional way, he jumps out of the crease, moves outside off and flicks it off the pad behind square
wasn't really expecting a fuller length, does not really move forward, bends to keep it out down the pitch
some release now, shortish and wide, Finch does not miss out, cuts in front of square and collects four
more rhythm in this back foot punch to mid off now from Finch
tries to walk out and clip it through midwicket but cannot time it, and chips it to mid on instead
rises and holds the line from short of a length, he adjusts and runs it to third man
loopy and full, not much power in the push as he plays it to the bowler
width again, but the length wasn't short enough, his punch finds point, Chatara has overstepped though
free hit arrives as a slower length ball into the pads, Finch swings, and the top edge flies over short fine leg
sharp retort from the bowler, he hits Finch on the right arm as the batsman is through with the pull just before the bouncer arrives
nice, he leans forward, pushes softly in front of cover and the single is comfortably taken
shot! that is all the way to where the Australian players are sitting, fuller length allows him to get under the ball and he holds the followthrough to watch it fly over the long on boundary
pushed to mid on off the front foot
another one, this one does not go as far as the previous one, but clears the long on rope comfortably, as Finch just casually picks this up from a full length
length ball defended to the off side
another no-ball as he digs it in back of a length, keeper dives to stop the tickle, and Haddin has to rush back in
Panyangara does well, finds the blockhole as Finch makes room to try and flay it down the ground, and then stops it in his followthrough
moves across to an offbreak and defends down the track
fuller one, defended off the front foot
straighter and skidding on, he leans forward to defend
moves across, and dabs this wider one past the lone slip
nice one, tossed up full around off, he gets forward in time
goes back this time to a length delivery and plays it out to off
tossed up full on the pad, nudged to midwicket
angled in down the pad, and straightens and bounces past the keeper
leans forward to push down the track
fuller, on middle and leg, knocked back to the bowler
skips out, Williams bowls it quicker into the pad, Haddin pushes to mid on
gets punished finally for that line, too far down the pad, and Finch connects with a powerful sweep, past short fine
much slower now, he makes some room on the back foot and works it to midwicket
nudged off the pad to short fine leg
spins in to leg from outside off, played out to midwicket
makes some room again and pushes to cover off the back foot
backs away even further to leg but cannot time it, also picks out extra cover
comes forward and works it with the spin to square leg
flays at this fuller delivery outside off, hasn't timed it, but hits the gap between extra cover and mid off
worked off the pad to square leg
fuller one on leg, he finds the man at square
makes lots of room outside leg and crashes it through extra cover, there is a man sweeping
Haddin looks to come out, the ball is angled in, and hits the pad to go to the keeper, who cannot collect it, there was a stumping chance for a brief instant there, but too much deviation off the pad
succeeds this time as this one is in his driving range, he reaches out and lofts it over midwicket
tries to slog-sweep, but was reaching for it in the end, and it runs off a thick edge past short fine
nudged straight to short fine off the pad, Finch has to get back
gives him a lot of width on this full delivery, and Finch has used his reach to clobber that over long on
on the back foot now to defend softly down the track
leans back and guides it to the sweeper
Haddin tries a big sweep again, and is beaten with one that wasn't too far from off
slight turn outside off, he stays on the crease and runs it to short third man
rocks back seeing a slightly shorter length and punches it past extra cover
quicker one played out to midwicket off the back foot
too full on the pad, he misses out as he tries to clip it square
down the leg side from Williams again, brushes the pad and rolls fine as he misses the sweep
pushed down to long on
lovely, Haddin takes a step out, gets right to the pitch, moves slightly inside the line and lofts gracefully over long off, holds the followthrough
turns it to midwicket, who parries it away with a dive, and they pinch a single meanwhile
allows it to turn in slowly and nudges it in front of square
bends right forward, and taps it to the leg side for one
some turn and bounce, but slow, and worked off the pad through square leg
punched to short midwicket off the back foot
tries to push it against the sharp incoming angle, chops it into the crease
angled in from wide of the crease, hits the pad high as Finch misses
uses the angle now to work it to deep backward square leg
walks out and has a drive at it, but ends up pushing outside the line
leaves the crease again, can only defend the length ball to the off side
overpitched and Haddin opens the face and times it superbly, but picks out backward point
shout for leg before first ball as Finch misses as he pushes forward, too high probably, that caught him on the flap
decides to come out of the crease, but misses again and is hit on the pad once more
another shout for lbw as he misses the sweep now, headed down leg possibly
and Finch breaks free after those appeals as he powers an overpitched ball through extra cover
tossed up on off stump, he is forward to block
jumps out, and whips it hard and straight to midwicket
slightly squared up with the incoming angle on this back of a length ball, squirts it out to point
whoa, he's walked out, and whipped this from way outside off, closing the face on it, back leg in the air, and clearing midwicket easily,
wanted to try it again, but not much as much angle on it and he has to play it out point
steers it to short third man for a single
would have been a wide had he not gone for it, stretched for it and bottom edged it along the ground to the keeper
full into the pad, Finch cannot get any bat on it with fine leg up
tries to nudge square with the turn but inside edges it onto pad
pushed to point off the front foot
he leans forward to a quicker one and pushes ti covers
makes some room to a flat one outside off and runs it past short third
full and angled across, he picks out cover with the drive
just past short leg as he moves across and works it off the pad
punches a length ball calmly to extra cover
they have hit some lovely sixes today, Haddin now walks out, an goes through with the lofted stroke, times it well enough to clear long off
uh oh, unfortunate way to go, Haddin defends this short of a length ball, it drops onto the pitch, bounces and as it comes down, it disodges the leg bail
gets across and defends a good length ball
flows forward to push a pitched up ball to mid on
gets on his toes and punches this short of a length ball through the covers
whips it off the pad to deep square leg
pushed to mid on off the front foot
moves across outside off and plays it out softly
tossed up high and full, he leans forward and pushes towards mid off
full again, driven to extra cover
flighted ball played out carefully to midwicket
leans forward and clips in the air in front of square, Taylor runs in from deep midwicket and keeps them to one
taps a short of a length ball to extra cover
that did not get up much, was angled in from wide of the crease, he is on the crease but gets bat down in time
now this one rises sharply as it is dug in short, he drops it on the pitch
on the crease to an incoming length ball now, has to defend hurriedly
comes forward now and keeps strike with a push past point
tossed up outside off stump, pushed to extra cover
tries to whip it fine but misses one turning down leg
knocked down to the bowler
pushes a tossed up delivery to extra cover, Marsh has got stuck here for a while
gets forward and tries to clip it past midwicket, finds the man
gets away this time, leaves the crease, isn't to the pitch, nudges it, fortunately for him it runs just past short leg
jumps out, and pushes it away off the pad, it pops up for a while, bowler fields
Marsh breaks free off this overpitched ball wide outside off, he lunges at it and cracks it between extra cover and mid off
shortish and wide now, but he is too far across and too eager on the cut to time it
softly pushes a length ball in front of covers for a single
short of a good length, defended down the track
steers a short of a length ball wide of the sweeper for two and that is fifty for Finch
wide length ball hit to the sweeper for a single
makes some room to a tossed up ball on off, but cannot get hold of it, picks up one to long off
better from Marsh, is off strike with a shuffle and a whip past the bowler to long on
floated up slowly, Finch leans forward, and defends off bat and pad
makes plenty of room but cannot beat the man at cover
slogs, but not much of a connection and the ball rolls to deep midwicket
shuffles across and misses one that spins across from outside off and carries down leg
slips it towards off with some angle on this length ball, defended back to him
pulls this short of a length ball from outside off, but off the bottom edge through square leg
on his toes to push a climbing short of a length ball to extra cover
coming in from back of a length, Marsh picks out extra cover with a forcing push
angled in and carries down the leg side as Marsh comes across and misses
good length ball defended down the track
nudged to widish leg slip
tries a big sweep and misses
length ball on middle and off, he makes a bit of room and taps it to cover
comes across, leans forward and drives hard, Chigumbura at extra cover cannot stop it, has taken a blow on his hand
nudged square on the leg side
drives a tossed up ball down to long off
pushes this back of a length ball to leg, midwicket rushes to his left to field
down the pads, and he whips it past Taylor at short fine leg, who holds a hand up for deep square, then decides to chase and slides to cut it off close to the rope
shortish and wide, and Marsh has taken half a step out and punched this superbly between extra cover and mid off
cramps him with an angled back of a length ball, defended down the track

there is a direct hit as they try to pinch a single on the off side, Finch stretches his bat in, the bat is on the line as the ball is just about to hit the stumps, and safely in when the next frame shows the bails are dislodged, nice reaction from the bowler to reach the ball and get rid of it quickly
turned through vacant midwicket but man from deep runs in and they are happy with one
punched to midwicket from the crease
sweeps off leg stump, fielded in the deep at fine leg
brings bat around front pad to nudge on the leg side for a sharp single
Marsh is not really in control as he jumps out and has a whack, slices it safely over covers in the end
stretches forward to push a tossed up ball to mid off
overpitched on the pad, tucked to deep midwicket
a push off the front foot to point, and they dash across for single
what a ripper, Finch pushes forward, and this turns and bounces past the edge and off stump
makes room and cuts hard off middle, stopped just inside the rope
slanted in fullish on the stumps, defended
angled in, nudged off the pad to square leg
comes across and whips off the pad, finds short fine leg
stays on the crease to a pitched up ball and square drives to backward point
poor ball, short, and sliding down the pad, he bends his knee and dispatches it between short fine leg and square leg
Finch has smoked this straight to backward square leg, this was set to disappear too, overpitched, on the pads, Finch bent for the sweep, and powered it to the fielder
walks out and smothers it down the pitch
pulled down to long on and he is away
pushed down the track
on the back foot to a length ball just outside off, pushes to point
leans right forward to push to cover
angled in full, he knocks it back to the bowler
full down the pads, he drags the sweep to short fine leg
on the front foot now to defend to off
carefully stretches forward and blocks one around off stump
cracks a sweep from well outside off stump, there is a man at deep backward square
waits on a tossed up length ball and whips it past midwicket from the crease
flatter one punched down to long on
presses forward to defend a flighted widish ball, bounce there for Nyumbu, hits bat close to the splice
full on middle and off, worked through midwicket, they make it back for the second safely
whipped from the crease to deep square leg
shuffles across and nudges it on the leg side for a quick run, there is an overthrow, but long off is around to stop it
full down the pads, swept and he picks the gap between short fine and square leg
length ball punched off middle to long on
could have been gone, he pushed to extra cover and set off for the single, Raza ran to his right but failed to gather the ball
Marsh escapes, he top edges the sweep, substitute Sibanda is some way up in the circle at short fine leg, he goes back and jumps, but it just clears him
played out to midwicket
pushed to extra cover
he's got hold of this alright, skips out, and lofts with a firm straight bat, makes a loud crack as it disappears over long on
pushed past the bowler's dive to long on
walks out and turns it straight to midwicket
angled in around off, he pushes forward, Bailey wants the single, but cover closes in
looks to have a go at it initially but then pushes to long off
leaves the crease, bowler shortens the length and he can only nudge it to midwicket
straightening on leg stump, swept to deep backward square
overpitched ball whipped straight to midwicket
angled in quicker into the pad, worked straight to short fine
leaves the crease and clips it down to long on
pulls down to deep backward square leg
walks out and tries to work it to leg but misses and is hit on the pad
looks to jump out again, but stays back and pulls to deep backward square leg
punches hard to the bowler it bursts out of his hands but no run given
punched off the back foot to long off
punches a length ball off the back foot to long off

Utseya has done superbly to hold on to this catch, Bailey had charged out inside the line and had a heave, sliced it behind point, from where Utseya set after it, Nyumbu tore in from short third man, it wasn't a head-on collision, but they did dash into each other, Utseya seems to have hurt himself
pushed down to long on for one
full down the leg side, and he sweeps hard, fine leg puts in a slide to save the boundary
full again on the pad, nudged square to leg for two more
leans forward to defend a length ball on off
swivels and forces a pull to short fine leg
fuller, worked off the pad to deep square leg
Maxwell lunges for one of his big sweeps, but does not connect well enough, single to long leg
whipped off the pad to deep square
in the air for a while but wide of midwicket as he works it square
overpitched down the pads, sweep finds long leg again
turns away from a length, punched to extra cover
he's not timed this, got too much elevation on the lofted push, and it has come down between extra cover and the sweeper
misses the reverse sweep, and somehow the ball misses leg stump
opens the face as he comes forward and picks up one to cover
angled in to the pad and pushed to long on
length ball pushed to the bowler
forces it down to long on and that is a maiden ODI fifty for Marsh, hasn't been flowing, but he's hung in
Maxwell tries and misses another reverse sweep, is hit on the body
he's decided to skip out this time, isn't really to the pitch but has gone dead straight and powerful over the bowler
makes room and has another go, thick inside edges past the keeper now
on middle and leg, worked to deep backward square
Maxwell swings and misses, keeper cannot collect, and short third does the stopping
now Marsh connects, he comes out, making some room too, and lifts it high over deep midwicket
punched down to long on
Maxwell has gone down on his knee and reverse hit this for six over deep point, incredible connection, he's been trying this for a while
tossed up into the pad, Maxwell cannot get under it and pushes it back
makes some room outside leg, Williams slows it up on middle and leg, and Maxwell can only push it away
chance gone, Marsh chipped this in the air as it bounced on him, Chigumbura was slow to move to his left from midwicket and it just eluded him in the end
sits up from a length down the leg side and Marsh opens up to hammer a pull over deep square leg
drags a pull down to short fine now
sitting up again from a shortish length, Marsh happily pulls once more, and picks the gap to the left of long leg
shortish once more, turning in from off now, but Marsh makes plenty of room outside leg and punches it hard through extra cover
overpitched, mid off is up, and Marsh has cranked up and drilled it past the fielder, what an over for Australia
poor start to the over, full and well outside the pad, Maxwell flays it past short fine
pitched up and widish outside off now, Maxwell bends forward and slices it high over backward point for four more
hit on the pad on the full as he misses the whip to leg, shout for lbw turned down, hit him in front of leg stump and was going down with all the angle
six more, low full toss on the pad and Maxwell's wrists have sent it soaring over the deep backward square boundary
there is no stopping them, full and wide outside off, Maxwell opens the face and lofts the drive over point
very low full toss, hard to get under it, Maxwell leans forward and pushes it to long on
Chatara starts with a slow, full and wide one, Maxwell has a swing, and slices it on the bounce to short third man
full and wide, Marsh stands with a foot planted forward and clobbers it over extra cover
cramps him with a back of a length ball slanted in, Marsh knocks it to the bowler
swings hard at this length ball outside off, gets it down to long off
slower length ball, he swings and misses, the ball goes just over leg stump
another slower one, but Maxwell has created this shot, he's shuffled right across and whipped it over short fine leg, and that is also his 50, off 28, the show is on indeed
slanted across around the blockhole, hit down to long off
more incredible stuff from Maxwell, he's fetched it from two feet outside off, and whipped it against the angle through square leg for four
full one guided behind point for a couple
in his slot this time on a length, and he's used his wrists so powerfully it has gone screaming in front of square
angled across wide, Maxwell reaches to have a drive and misses
four more, tries to hit the blockhole outside off, but Maxwell slices it to the fine third man boundary, just beating the fielder
carnage from both ends continues, Marsh walks out, Chatara digs it short, and Marsh pulls in front of square, and comfortably over the boundary
the stand ends at a blistering 109 off 54 as Marsh fails to clear long on with this slower length ball
yorker turned through vacant midwicket, they take on the man from the deep and make it for the second
he makes room outside leg, Chatara follows him with a full ball but Maxwell opens the face and flays it to the deep point boundary for four more
for once, he picks out the off side infield and cannot clear point
pulled hard to deep midwicket, Smith scrambles back for the second
mistimes a push off a wide length ball but gets off strike nevertheless
swings at and misses this slower short ball, bounces in front of the keeper
walks across to a very full one on the stumps and drills it just past the umpire
makes room and cracks it straight to mid off, Smith is half way up for the single, and Raza sends him back with a direct hit
the show carries on, Maxwell is down on his knee before the length ball arrives outside off, and he top edges the reverse hit fine on the off side
appeal for leg before turned down as Maxwell skips across and misses a whip
full and slanted in, he gets front leg out of the way and clips it to long on
slower one pitched up, Maxwell waits on it and pummels it straight, one bounce and it crashes into the sightscreen
this short one sits up, and Maxwell hammers it flat over wide long on to move into the 90s

does not matter what the format is, Maxwell loves the 90s, he cranked up for another six, this was pitched up and he connected too, but sent it soaring high up, long off does superbly to judge it and goes down with the take
takes a single to extra cover as he pushes a length ball
length on the pad, he nudges it to short fine leg
slower length ball pushed to vacant midwicket, bowler fumbles as he goes after it, but keeps them to one
tries to pull this short ball, but misses and is hit on the body
Mitchell pulls this time and beats short fine leg's dive
full and wide, too wide, says the umpire
Johnson's shattered the glass panel of the commentary box as he lifts a pitched up delivery straight over the bowler, Pommie Mbangwa gets up and brushes some shrapnel off his clothes
tries to pull a slower short ball but cannot connect and it rolls behind square
slips it full down the leg side
Faulkner swings and misses but Chatara has bowled a no-ball now
another miss as this full toss is angled in and hits him low on the pad
low full toss, makes a nice, loud sound as Johnson sends it dead straight again, along the ground this time
has a go at this wide one angled across and misses, but Chatara will have to bowl it again
loses his shape this time as Chatara sends down a loopy, full slower one just outside off stump
short ball sits up outside off and is pulled away dismissively to the deep midwicket boundary
shout for leg before turned down as Johnson misses a full one on the walk across
Faulkner weighs in the last ball of the innings as he cracks a full delivery to the straight boundary

inn2.comm: swings towards the pads from leg stump, Mawoyo is struck on the pad as he was beaten by pace
into the pads again, Mawoyo wants to flick it to the leg side but fails
swing and a miss outside off this time! It was a quick delivery, full and wide, Mawoyo went for a big swing and missed it
on length outside off, steered to third man to get off the mark
welcomes Raza with a bouncer! It was banged in on leg stump and Raza ducked under it just in time
length delivery outside off and angling away, Raza lets it go
length delivery not too far from the off stump, Mawoyo shoulders arms for that

given straightaway! Starc strikes on his second ball. He pitched it right on middle stump on length and Mawoyo was struck on the front pad by the delivery that came in slightly as he was stuck to his crease
outside off on length and he lets it go
another loud appeal, but this wasn't as close! This one pitched on leg stump and was heading down leg as the batsmen looked to flick it to leg side. The umpire was unmoved
outside off again on length, let alone
tad short of length outside off, Masakadza defends on the off side
fullish delivery outside off, pushed to point by Raza and a misfield would have given them a run but they decide against it
that was quick! Bangs in a bouncer outside off and that flies away to the keeper
back of length delivery angling away from outside off, Raza chases and misses
on length this time outside off, he doesn't want to chase this one
nearly got him! Back of length on off with bounce, Raza is cemented to his crease in an attempt to defend but he misses it
full and wide with a lot of pace, left alone and that's a maiden
length delivery on leg stump with some inswing, goes to the leg side off the pad
outside off now and some room allows Masakadza to get off the mark by helping it down to third man
attempted yorker is a low full toss outside off, Raza drives it to cover and they had to run very quickly to complete the run. Raza also off the mark
short ball on middle and leg, no room and time for Masakadza to pull or defend to the leg side
it's too short and there's room, Masakadza gets the upper cut out of his bag for a six! It was outside off, not too wide, and Masakadza helped it with the pace to make it sail over third man
short of length outside off, punched off the back foot between point and cover point for two more. Productive over for Zimbabwe
short of length outside off, he cuts and gets a bottom edge to slip after a couple of bounces
short and quick just outside off, swings away further as Raza ducks and sways out of line
full and too wide, tapped towards third slip with a horizontal bat
short of length on middle stump, Raza hops back and defends on the off side
on length outside off, MJ rolls his fingers over that one and Raza is happy to leave it
another one outside off and swinging away further, left alone again. Second maiden in a row
outside off to start with, he lets it go
coming in this time towards the batsman from length, he pushes it back to the bowler
length delivery outside off, solid defence towards cover point
outside off, pushed without moving his feet much and cover point dives to his left to save a few runs
length delivery outside off, pushed on the off side again, off the front foot this time
short and wide this time and Masakadza looks to cut but misses. Another maiden
length delivery outside off and angling away, Raza lets it go
looked a touch slower and it was closer to off stump, Raza wanted to play and withdrew his bat a bit too late
well outside off with some outswing, left alone by the batsman
goes down the leg side for a wide this time
another wide - this one way outside off even though Raza chased it
gets it right - length delivery outside off and Raza leaves it
touch closer to the off stump with some outswing, Raza leaves again
even closer and beats the outside edge! This one pitched on off, short of length, Raza stayed on the back foot to defend and missed it
short and wide, Masakadza dances down the track and smashes it over the covers for a four. He only had to clear the infield even if he didn't middle it
wide outside off again, not that short, Masakadza cuts, seeing the width but gets a bottom edge towards point
short of length ball coming in from outside off, Masakadza taps it off the back foot to point for a quick single
bouncer nearly gets the helmet! Raza took evasive action for the short ball, took his eyes off the ball but protected his face with the bat
he was expecting another short one and made room for this one, swatting it over point for a four
oh one more! Almost a replay as Raza makes room again and middles this one even better, with a cracking cut over backward point for four more
beaten! Back of length on the of stump, Masakadza wants to defend with an open face but the angle beats him
in the air, but wide of point. Masakadza played the length delivery on the up outside off and it went to third man for one

superb timing from Raza as he crunches this one off the back foot, Lyon runs to the boundary and dives to cut it in, but the ball might still fall outside the boundary and Maxwell also dives over the boundary to finally cut it in. but they have run four till then
angles it in from outside off, Raza defends off the back foot
slightly short outside off, runs it to third man for one
from outside leg, tucked to midwicket off the back foot
that's in the air and clear mid-off easily! It was full on middle and Raza merely looked to dig it out but he got enough to easily get four down the ground
yorker on the off stump, inside edge goes to the leg side
Haddin jumps with joy thinking there was an edge as Raza went back to cut the short ball, which he missed, but there was daylight between bat and ball. Richardson didn't appeal at all
makes a lot of room, upper-cuts the short ball from outside off to third man
angled it in sharply from outside off, and gets a thick inside edge onto his pad
another one angled in, flicked off the pads to deep square leg for one
starts with a length delivery outside off, Masakadza watches it go to the keeper

comes down the track and smashes it down the ground for a one-bounce four! He struck that pretty well over the bowler's head as it was pitched up. They are targeting the relatively inexperienced right-handed bowlers
he tries to pull the back of length ball outside off but is hit on the thigh pad
coming in from outside off, defends to cover off the back foot
pulls it this time, and it falls just out of reach of Johnson at mid-on. He didn't middle it that well and it went high, Johnson ran to his right but it was a bit too far
tries a cross-batted slog on the leg side and missed the ball outside off

what turn on the first ball! He pitched it on length outside off, Raza put his left foot forward for a big drive but the turn deceived him and a faint edge went between the keeper and the batsman for three
leans forward to defend it from outside off
tossed up outside off, he comes down to drive the full toss down ton long-on
turning in form outside off, he goes back this time to tap it to the leg side
flighted outside off, drives down the ground with the turn to long-on for one
he comes down the track and hits it to long-off where there's nobody in the deep! It was outside off and Raza lofted it down the ground for a one-bounce four. 10 from that over
short of length outside off, defends off the back foot to point
short ball on leg, pulled powerfully to deep fine leg for one
on length very close to off stump, he stays back and defends it towards point
short ball, outside off, pulled off the back foot to deep midwicket
short of length outside off, defends it off the back foot on the off side
towards the leg stump and they take a leg bye as it goes off the pad on the leg side
takes a step down and drives it to long-on
tossed up outside off and Raza drives it inside out in the air over the covers for a clean four! He's not letting Lyon settle down
Lyon goes shorter and Raza goes back to help it behind square on the leg side for a quick one
slightly full on middle and leg, tucked to deep square leg for one
short of length and coming in, punched off the back foot straight to cover

Lyon's broken the stand with a soft dismissal! He pitched it up on off and Raza went down on a knee to sweep it straight to backward square leg in the circle to Mitchell Marsh. Raza drops his head in disappointment but he has to walk back after a useful stand
short ball close to off stump, Masakadza looks to hook but it goes over his bat
short of length on middle and leg, turned off the back foot past midwicket and he calls for two straightaway
short and wide, crunched off the back foot to sweeper cover for one
back of length on off, he hops back and defends it on off side
on length just outside off, Taylor defends off the back foot again
short ball outside off, Taylor looks to help it to third man over slip but misses
comes down a step and turns the ball from outside off to midwicket
tossed up on off, he drives it softly towards long-on but Maxwell at midwicket dives to his left to stop it
shorter now and Masakadza goes back to play it behind square on leg side
there's a gap there and he picks it! Takes out the reverse sweep and places it behind point on the of side in the big gap
big appeal for the sweep but it struck him way outside off
another reverse sweep and another four! This one was fuller and closer to off and Taylor swept it fine on the off side for four more
short of length outside off, Masakadza stays back and defends on the leg side
short ball from wide of the crease, Masakadza taps it off the back foot as first slip fetches it
fuller outside off and Masakadza drives it straight to cover
angles it in from outside off, Masakadza hops back and defends
banged in short but it's going down leg and Masakadza gets enough bat while pulling to run it fine down the leg side to beat fine leg for four
width on offer, Masakadza looks to cut but gets a bottom edge and that's drinks
outside off, it's helped to point off the back foot and there's not enough time for a run
length delivery around off stump, he leans forward to defend it on off
on length on the off stump, he defends it back
chipped in the air with a flick off the pads for two
length delivery on the off stump again, he defends it to cover
angling away just outside off, tapped to point off the back foot
full, angling in towards off, and he comes forward and opens his bat face to dab it down to third man
back of a length, angling across, and he goes back and across to defend towards cover

gone! This one was on a similar length to the previous ball, but it bounced a lot more, and he pushed at it without really looking to do anything in particular. It was halfway uppercut, halfway dab, and the ball bounced out of Finch's upraised hands at first slip before he recovered to cling on, tumbling all the way
back of length on off, defends off the back foot on off
full delivery outside off, pushed tentatively without footwork to cover
short ball outside off and swinging away, left easily for the keeper
bangs in the short ball on middle and leg, Masakadza takes his eyes off and the ball goes over him
outside off this time and he defends off the front foot to cover
short of length from middle and angling away, punched off the back foot to point
slower delivery is a low full toss outside off, pushed down to mid-off for one
back of length outside off, pushed off the back foot to point
on the middle stump without any movement, he defends it back
full and outside off, pushed off the front foot to sweeper cover
length delivery around off and Chigumbura defends off the front foot
looks to make some room, Mitch pitches it short on middle and leg and Chigumbura hops on his toes to defend on the off side
length delivery on middle and off, Chigumbura defends it back to the bowler
nearly in the block hole on off stump, he digs it down to mid-off
hit on the helmet! It was short and quick, as usual from MJ, Chigumbura looked to sway out of the line but the ball chased him and hit him bang in the helmet before going to third man
the short ball has worked! Faulkner banged it in as Chigumbura pulled but only managed a leading edge high in the air, Haddin went back a few steps and pouched it in his gloves
another short ball - around the leg stump and it's tucked off the back foot behind square on the leg side
short of length on off, Williams stays back and defends
full around off and Williams drives it down handsomely to mid-off
another edge off the short ball, this falls safe! It was going towards Williams' ribs as he stayed back to play an awkward pull and got a leading edge to fall short of deep fine leg
length ball on off, tapped off the front foot to cover

strikes first ball of the new spell! It was angling away from Williams from back of length and he pushed it off the back foot straight to cover for an easy catch as if it was a fielding drill. Five down now Zimbabwe
around the of stump off length, he defends it back
just outside off and he runs it fine to third man to get off the mark
touch short of length outside off, pushed to cover off the back foot
fuller outside off, Masakadza taps it with soft hands on off for a single but Mutumbami sends him back as point ran to his left to collect the ball
touch wider outside off, tapped to point off the back foot
turns it in from outside off, he goes back to defend it
tossed up well outside off, Mutumbami looks to drive but can't middle it
touch shorter and closer to off, Mutumbami sweeps it to deep fine leg
flighted outside off and Masakadza sweeps it fine down the leg side to beat the fine-leg fielder for four
flighted on off, tucked with the turn to short fine leg for one
flighted well outside off and it's too full this time as Mutumbami drives it through the covers for four! 10 runs from that over
punched off the back foot from outside off, Maxwell dives to his left at cover to stop it with one hand
angled into the pads, tucked to midwicket by Masakadza and he shouts 'no' three times
slower one and it's short outside off, Masakadza waits for it and upper-cuts it fine on the off side to bring up his team's 100
angled in from outside off, Masakadza replies with a solid defence
touch fuller outside off, he drives it to sweeper cover for one run
short of length on off, he hops back to defend it on leg
flighted outside off, tucked to midwicket
wider outside off and full, pushed down to cover
comes down the track for the flatter delivery, turned to backward square leg for one
flighted outside off, Mutumbami goes for a big sweep but misses it completely
on length outside off, he presses forward and blocks
comes down and drives the full delivery down to long-on for one
full delivery outside off, driven straight to cover
coming in form length outside off, Mutumbami leans forward to defend it
bouncer towards middle and leg and he ducks under it
betas him completely with the swing and Haddin completes a fantastic take! It was short of length outside off and came in sharply to go through the gate and Haddin caught it with his left hand
stifled appeal for lbw as Mutumbami is struck in front of leg stump but it was going down with the angle
angled into the batsman, tucked off the hips to square leg
flighted around off stump, tucked with the turn to midwicket
tossed up a touch wider, he drives it down to long-on for one
flatter delivery on middle, swept to deep backward square leg for one
on leg stump, Masakadza wanted to play it fine down leg but it went off his pad
flighted around off and Masakadza taps it past midwicket for his fifty, his 24th in ODIs
flighted outside off, pushed to midwicket who tries for a chance at non-striker's end and concedes an overthrow
sends this one down leg for a wide
angled in towards off stump, thick inside edge goes down to deep fine leg
full outside off and he smashes it down the ground for a powerful four past the bowler
bangs in a bouncer and Masakadza ducks under it
angles in another short ball towards the batsman and he sways out of the line
another wide down the leg side, Haddin dives a long way to get a hand to it as they also run one
nearly a block hole on middle, pushed down straight to mid-on
angled in towards the batsman, nudged to deep fine leg for one
quick and flat delivery, he comes down and takes it on his pads
outside off, it's pushed to cover off the front foot
loud appeal for lbw and it's given! Mutumbami shuffled across towards off, the ball pitched on off and turned in to hit him in front of the stumps and the finger went up
he presses forward and blocks the ball outside off
puts his left leg forward and defends it again outside off
defends the ball from length around off to the leg side
outside off with the angle, he leans forward and defends
bouncer on the leg stump, Masakadza doesn't move much and lets it go
takes a step down and taps the ball from outside leg towards square leg
straight delivery on middle stump, an outside edge runs down to third man
short ball on leg, tucked off the hips to deep fine leg
short of length and coming in, he defends it to cover point
outside off and turning away, cut off the back foot to sweeper cover
tossed up on off, driven straight to cover
shorter and outside off with the leg spin again, punched to sweeper cover
flighted just outside off, swept against the turn to deep fine leg
drives it in the air, just wide of cover. He played it on the up with the turn form outside off to sweeper cover for one
tossed up again outside off, punches the drive towards wide long-off and calls for two immediately
presses forward for the ball well outside off and helps it fine down to third man for one
gives himself room and manages an edge over the keeper's head for four! He was looking to cut it and the bounce took the outside edge
slower ball from the back of the hand on leg stump, flicked off the pads past midwicket
on length on middle, he defends it towards the bowler
angled in to him, flicked with the angle to the leg side for one more
full delivery on the stumps and it's pushed down to mid-on for a quick single. It's time for drinks
comes down the track for a slog and gets a thick leading edge to clear mid-on and it lands safe for two runs
sweeps this one from outside off to deep fine leg for two more
gone this time! He was coming down the track too often and this time the turn beat him past the slog he tried and was way down the track when Haddin stumped him
presses forward to block but the turn beats the outside edge

there's a stumping appeal only from Haddin as he took his time to whip the bails off! The batsmen was beaten again by the turn, his back foot was inside but went in the air for a bit but it was back again by the time the bails were taken off
short and flat outside off, cut to cover point as they look for a single but George Bailey's inaccurate throw goes to slip and Panyangara survives again
short of length outside off, helped to third man by opening the face of the bat
short of length outside off, left alone by the batsman
short ball, he pulls it slightly in the air, bit late on the shot, and it goes wide of midwicket
on length outside off, he leans forward to push it to cover
slower ball from the back of the hand is full outside off, thick inside edge runs down to deep fine leg
full on leg stump, drives it off the pads to midwicket
short of length outside off with a lot of turn, punched off the back foot to cover
turn again outside off, cut to point this time
he stays back and lets it turn again to cut it, short cover does well to stop it
slightly fuller and pushed off the back foot again
tossed up outside off, chipped down the ground to long-off
flighted on off, thick edge goes off the bat to the off side
short of length outside off, Utseya stays back to defend it
fuller and just outside off, pushed down to mid-on
goes down the leg side with the angle for a wide
fuller outside off and pushed down to mid-on again
short ball and pulled powerfully with authority to deep midwicket but there's a man there
full and outside off, he drives and misses it
what a yorker, the stumps go flying! It was coming in sharply with the angle, Panyangara tried to defend but it went right through him and sent the middle and leg stumps for a walk
flighted outside off, pushed off the front foot to cover
short and flat just outside off, cut off the back foot to point
short and even wider, he packs another punch off the back foot but can't clear the packed off side
he hands a simple catch to mid-on from outside off! It turned away again from the batsman, Utseya went back to pull it but failed to middle it and handed an easy one to Starc at mid-on
short and flat, he's bowling too many of these, and the batsman swats it to the long-on boundary for four since there's nobody in the deep
wider outside off after the turn, swatted towards long-off in the air this time for one
right in the block hole again and Chatara blocks is back
low full toss, nearly in the block hole, on middle stump, blocked again with an inside edge
angled sharply into the batsman, tucked to deep square leg and that takes them to 150
on length on off stump, Nyumbu defends it back
down the leg side with the angle for a wide
bangs in a short ball outside off with some swing, the batsman sways out of the way
on length and angled in from outside off, tapped wide of mid-on for a quick single
sharp turn outside off, swished off the back foot to extra cover
looks to cut it off the back foot after the turn but misses the outside edge
it's all over now, Smith takes three! It was pitched up on middle and leg, Nyumbu went for a slog and a leading edge ballooned to point for an easy catch to end the match
